## On the nav header

With your other decisions folded in, the header on every page looks like:

```
← Back     EN · NL · 🔍
```

- **EN** links to `../../index.html` (or `../index.html` from `nl/`)
- **NL** links to `../../nl/index.html`
- **🔍** links to `../../search-en.html` (EN pages) or `../../search-nl.html` (NL pages)
- The auto-generated nav list appears below the header, above the page content

This keeps the language switch and search together in one consistent spot on every page, generated automatically — nothing to maintain manually.

